com.sap.cloud.sdk.cloudplatform.connectivity

Interface HttpDestination

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DestinationProperties, HttpDestinationProperties
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractHttpDestination, ClientCredentialsHttpDestination, CustomTokenHttpDestination, DefaultHttpDestination, ScpCfHttpDestination, ScpNeoHttpDestination

    public interface HttpDestination
extends HttpDestinationProperties
    Platform independent representation of a HTTP destination as a collection of key-value pairs.

    Additionally provides an easy way to decorate itself with a given decorator function.

    • Method Detail

      • decorate

        @Nonnull
default <TargetT extends HttpDestinationProperties> TargetT decorate(@Nonnull
                                                                              Function<HttpDestinationProperties,TargetT> decorator)
        Provides an convenient way to decorate this destination with a custom class. Note: You must use the returned value in your code to apply the decorated functionality.

        Example usage: 

         {
     CustomDestination customDestination = destination.decorate(CustomDestination::new);
 }
        Type Parameters:
        TargetT - The type of the decorated destination.
        Parameters:
        decorator - The decorator function to apply. Should not return null.
        Returns:
        The return value of this destination applied to the given decorator function.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the provided decorator returns null.
